To construct this website from scratch using HTML, you would first create the structure using HTML tags. Here is an improved and detailed outline:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>JLaughter - Ficlets Archive</title>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: "Georgia", "Times New Roman", "Times", serif;
      background-color: #fff;
      color: #000;
      margin: 0;
    }
    header, footer {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      max-width: 1024px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 20px;
    }
    nav ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 0;
      display: flex;
    }
    nav ul li {
      margin-right: 10px;
    }
    main {
      max-width: 1024px;
      margin: 50px auto 0;
      padding: 20px;
    }
    .author-meta, .item-meta, .bio, footer nav {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1><a>Ficlets</a></h1>
    <nav>
      <ul>
        <li><a>Authors</a></li>
        <li><a>Stories</a></li>
        <li><a>Tags</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>
  </header>
  <main>
    <article class="author-meta">
      <h1>JLaughter</h1>
      <section class="bio">
        <p>I’ve always been an avid (dare I say: <span class="caps">OBSESSED</span>) reader...</p>
        <!-- Continue with the rest of the mentioned bio -->
      </section>
    </article>
    <section class="stories">
      <h2>Stories (79)</h2>
      <ul class="object-list stories-list">
        <li class="story-list-item">
          <div class="item-meta">
            <h3><a>Bagman: A Clear Blue Spike</a></h3>
            <p><strong>Author:</strong> <a>JLaughter</a></p>
            <p>Published <abbr title="2008-05-14 01:46:07 UTC">May 14th, 2008</abbr></p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <!-- Add other stories in a similar manner -->
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>
  <footer>
    <aside><a>Ficlets</a></aside>
    <section>
      <p>All stories are licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 License.</p>
      <nav>
        <ul>
          <li><a>Authors</a></li>
          <li><a>Stories</a></li>
          <li><a>Tags</a></li>
        </ul>
      </nav>
    </section>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

This HTML provides an improved and more structured outline for the website, incorporating better practices for modern web design, such as meta tags for character settings and responsive design.
